第一組：生活與建議 (Aid, Advice, Advise, Allow, Avoid, Answer)

The government provides financial aid to people in need. (政府為有需要的人提供經濟援助。)
Thank you for your helpful advice. (謝謝你實用的建議。)
advise: I advise you to see a doctor as soon as possible. (我建議你盡快去看醫生。)
allow: My parents don't allow me to stay out late. (我父母不允許我在外面待太晚。)
avoid: We should avoid making the same mistake again. (我們應該避免再犯同樣的錯誤。)
answer: Can you answer the phone for me? (你能幫我接一下電話嗎？)

第二組：職場與商業 (Affair, Advantage, Advertise, Advertisement, Agreement, Aim)
affair: It's a private affair, so I can't tell you much. (這是私事，所以我不能跟你說太多。)
advantage: Taking this course will give you a big advantage. (上這門課會給你帶來很大的優勢。)
advertise: They advertise their new products on social media. (他們在社交媒體上為新產品做廣告。)
advertisement: I saw an advertisement for a job in the newspaper. (我在報紙上看到一個徵人廣告。)
agreement: We finally reached an agreement after long hours of talk. (經過長時間的對談，我們終於達成協議。)
aim: Our main aim is to improve customer service. (我們的主要目標是提升客戶服務。)

第三組：交通與旅行 (Airline, Airport, Arrival, Arrive, Around, Ahead, Along)
airline: Which airline are you flying with? (你搭乘哪家航空公司的班機？)
airport: I will pick you up at the airport. (我會去機場接你。)
arrival: Please check the arrival time of the flight. (請查詢航班的到達時間。)
arrive: What time did you arrive home last night? (你昨晚幾點到家的？)
around: Let’s meet around 6 o'clock. (我們 6 點左右見面吧。)
ahead: There is a gas station just ahead. (前面就有一個加油站。)
along: Walk along this street and turn left. (沿著這條街走，然後左轉。)

第四組：情緒與互動 (Anxious, Argue, Agree, Alike, Against, Affect)
anxious: She is anxious about her job interview tomorrow. (她對明天的面試感到焦慮。)
argue: Please don't argue with me about this. (請不要為了這件事跟我爭論。)
agree: I completely agree with your opinion. (我完全同意你的觀點。)
alike: The two brothers look very alike. (這對兄弟長得很像。)
against: Are you for or against the new plan? (你支持還是反對這個新計畫？)
affect: The weather will affect our travel plans. (天氣會影響我們的旅遊計畫。)

第五組：數量與時間 (Amount, Altogether, Another, Already, All, Age, Ago, Again)
amount: A large amount of money was spent on the project. (這個專案花費了大量的資金。)
altogether: That will be 50 dollars altogether. (那總共是 50 美元。)
another: Would you like another cup of coffee? (你想再喝一杯咖啡嗎？)
already: I have already finished my homework. (我已經做完功課了。)
all: All students must wear uniforms. (所有學生都必須穿制服。)
age: He started playing the piano at the age of five. (他在五歲時開始彈鋼琴。)
ago: I graduated from college five years ago. (我五年前大學畢業。)
again: Could you say that again, please? (能請你再說一遍嗎？)

第六組：其他 (Average, Area, Alarm, Among, After)
average: The average temperature in July is 30 degrees. (七月的平均氣溫是 30 度。)
area: This is a quiet residential area. (這是一個安靜的住宅區。)
alarm: My alarm goes off at 7 a.m. every morning. (我的鬧鐘每天早上 7 點響。)
among: She is very popular among her classmates. (她在同學之間很受歡迎。)
after: We can go for a movie after dinner. (晚餐後我們可以去看電影。)
